711612f-a.text:
22nd street, south side, west from No. 442 West 22nd Street, between Ninth and Tent Avenues. The two and a half story brick house, 462 West 22nd Street, is believed to have been the residence of Bishop Clement C. Moore, author of "The Night Before Christmas", and builder of the first London Terrace.

June 28, 1928.
